{
  "stem": "26111.4",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They must have thought she was crazy at first, as [LAUGHS] traditional and conservative as the British are, especially the-- especially at Oxford.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And-- but there she is.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "She talked them around to it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And the result was that the most important subjects were taught both in German and in English so that I had fairly fluent, fluent English by the time I got there.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Strong accent, I suppose, somewhat, but I, I, I wasn't as lost as somebody that wouldn't know English.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And when you learn about English history and English things, life, et cetera, you know a little bit about the country.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So-- and I'd always had a very great respect for it and, and interest in it.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So much of the literature that I read had been originally-- well, when I read it before I started to learn English, I read it in German.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There were translations, and, and-- whether they came from English or American authors.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And so it, it, it meant something positive to me.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But in any case, the main thing at that particular time was that I was going from a bloody dictatorship and from oppression, which it was, to a free country.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That was the-- oppression and freedom that was really the--",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, I knew that pretty well from the beginning.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, I can.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] my-- the only one from my family who could take me to the station was my father because my mother had been very, very ill with asthma for some weeks before, had been in hospital for several weeks, was recuperating at the house of a friend.",
      "word_count": 51
    }
  ],
